'''Ninnidh''' (tamien coincido por '''Ninnidh l Pio''', an eirlandés: '''Ninnidh leth derc''', que senefica Ninnidh dun uolho) fui un santo crestiano eirlandés de l seclo VI. San Ninnidh ye un de ls duoze Apóstelos de la Eirlanda.<ref>[https://aleteia.org/2018/03/01/who-were-the-12-apostles-of-ireland/ Who were the ’12 Apostles of Ireland’?]</ref> El ye associado a la cuosta de Lough Erne i particularmente a la ilha Inishmacsaint i la Knockninny, Cundado de Fermanagh, na Eirlanda de l Norte. 18 de Janeiro ye l die de la sue celebraçon.

Ninnidh de Inicmacsaint ye quemummente cunfundido cul Santo Ninnidh de la Pura Mano, que stubo cun Brígida de la Eirlanda ne l sou leito de muorte.<ref>[https://orthodoxmissions.wordpress.com/category/saints/ St. Makarii Glukharev, Missionary to the Altai]</ref><ref>[https://books.google.pt/books?id=9h4OAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA115&lpg=PA115&dq=st+ninnidh&source=bl&ots=a21B1-Rg3N&sig=uz5hvc5_RBNnZol0UDG_EYagc2I&hl=en&sa=X&ei=TfB8U6DvHJTLsQSRi4GAAw&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=st%20ninnidh&f=false Ulster Journal of Archaeology]</ref>

